> This Chicken Thighs in Creamy Pesto Sauce is a crowd pleaser and is one to get the family round the dinner table for. Super simple to make, and easily customised to suit the kids too.

Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel).

Pop the chunks onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{drizzle}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, sprinkle over the @dried oregano{1%tsp}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

In the meantime, peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

In a large #bowl{}, add the @British chicken thighs{3}, garlic, @lemon & herb seasoning{2%tbsp} and a good drizzle of @olive oil{drizzle}.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once the pan is hot, lay the chicken thighs flat in the pan.

Fry until browned all over, ~{3-4%minutes} each side.

Once the chicken is browned, lay them onto a baking tray lined with #foil{}.

Bake on the middle shelf of your oven until cooked through, ~{12-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, wipe out the panel used for the chicken thighs.

When the potatoes have 5 mins left, return the (now empty) pan to medium-high heat with a drizzle of oil.

Once hot, add the @peas{120%g} and stir-fry for ~{2-3%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Transfer the peas to a bowl and leave to one side. Cover with a #lid{} or foil to keep warm.

Return the panel to medium-high heat and add the @creme fraiche{75%g}, @fresh pesto{32%g} and @water for the sauce{75%ml}. Stir to combine, bring to a boil, then lower the heat and simmer until piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}. Add a splash of water if it's a little too thick.

When everything's ready, share the chicken thighs between your plates. Serve the roasted potatoes and peas alongside.

Finish by spooning the creamy pesto sauce over your chicken.

Enjoy!